'''Artcyclopedia''' is an online [[database]] of museum-quality [[fine art]] founded by [[Canadians|Canadian]] John Malyon.

==Information==
The Artcyclopedia only deals with art that can be viewed online, and indexes 2,300 art sites (from museums and galleries), with links to around 180,000 artworks by 8,500 renowned [[artists]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.artcyclopedia.com/ Artcyclopedia home page], November 2006.&lt;/ref&gt; The site has also started to compile a list of [[art galleries]] and [[auction]] houses.

