* '''[[1953 in literature|1954]]:''' No award  given{{efn|group=notes|The two-man fiction jury could not agree on a single book to recommend to the Advisory Board, so no award was given; among the books recommended by juror Eric P. Kelly were ''Ramey'' by [[Jack D. Ferris]], ''The Sands of Karakorum'' by [[James Ramsey Ullman|James Ullman]], ''[[The Adventures of Augie March]]'' by [[Saul Bellow]], and ''The Four Lives of Mundy Tolliver'' by [[Ben Lucien Burman]], while juror Harris F. Fletcher recommended ''The Street of the Three Friends'' by [[Myron Brinig]] and ''The Deep Sleep'' by [[Wright Morris]]&lt;ref name=&quot;hohenberg&quot; /&gt;}}
