* '''[[1970 in literature|1971]]:''' No award given{{efn|group=notes|name=1971award|The three novels the Pulitzer committee put forth for consideration to the Pulitzer board were: ''[[Losing Battles]]'' by [[Eudora Welty]]; ''[[Mr. Sammler's Planet]]'' by [[Saul Bellow]]; and ''[[The Wheel of Love]]'' by [[Joyce Carol Oates]]. The board rejected all three and opted for no award.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite book|title=Novel/Fiction Awards 1917–1994: From Pearl S. Buck and Margaret Mitchell to Ernest Hemingway and John Updike|date=1997|publisher=K.G. Saur|last=Fischer|first=Heinz Dietrich|last2=Fischer|first2=Erika J.|isbn=9783110972115|location=München|oclc=811400780|pages=LX-LXI|series=The Pulitzer Prize Archive|volume=10 (in part D, &quot;Belles Lettres&quot;)}}&lt;/ref&gt;}}
