* '''[[1976 in literature|1977]]:''' No award given{{efn|group=notes|name=1977award|The fiction jury had recommended the 1977 award to [[Norman MacLean]]'s ''[[A River Runs Through It (novel)|A River Runs Through It]]'', but the Pulitzer board, which has sole discretion for awarding the prize, made no award. That same year, however, [[Alex Haley]]'s iconic [[family saga]] ''[[Roots (novel)|Roots]]'' was awarded a special Pulitzer Prize.&lt;ref name=&quot;controversies&quot; /&gt;}}
** ''[[A River Runs Through It (novel)|A River Runs Through It]]'' by [[Norman MacLean]]
** ''[[Roots: The Saga of an American Family|Roots]]'' by [[Alex Haley]] (special Pulitzer Prize)
